<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFF2FFD8FF6BFBE4FD4EFEC3" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="316" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF2FFD9FF6BFBE4FE75FBE9" blockId="40.[151,1127,1026,1625]" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FF6BFBE4FEB8FBA9" bold="true" box="[151,262,1026,1049]" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Remarks.</emphasis>
As I mentioned under 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FDFEFBE4FDCCFBA9" box="[514,626,1026,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FDFEFBE4FDCCFBA9" box="[514,626,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. postica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD09FBE4FCFBFBA9" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[757,837,1026,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD09FBE4FCFBFBA9" box="[757,837,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are extremely variable regarding dorsal pattern and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FE49FBC4FD92FB89" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[437,556,1058,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FE49FBC4FD92FB89" box="[437,556,1058,1081]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is another case where individual colour morphs were described as distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF2FFD9FF49FB84FCD2FA49" blockId="40.[151,1127,1026,1625]" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FF49FB84FED6FBC9" author="BOHEMAN" box="[181,360,1122,1145]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN (1862)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FE21FB84FD0BFBC9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[477,693,1122,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FE21FB84FD0BFBC9" box="[477,693,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Coptocycla wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presumably based on a single specimen with mostly yellow colouration and disc of elytra with irregular and coalescent black patches (see 
<figureCitation id="77ED62B3FFF2FFD9FF34FB44FEBBFB09" box="[200,261,1186,1209]" captionStart="Figs 1–3" captionStartId="12.[151,187,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[216,1090,220,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-32@12.[161,1116,219,1542]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 1–3. Charidotis amazona sp. nov., holotype 1 – dorsal aspect; 2 – lateral aspect; 3 – head, antennae, and fore legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305727/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
Fig. 
<quantity id="282ED3D3FFF2FFD9FF04FB44FEBBFB09" box="[248,261,1186,1209]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FEDAFB44FE71FB09" author="CHAMPION" box="[294,463,1186,1209]" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION 1894</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FE23FB44FD2FFB09" author="WAGENER" box="[479,657,1186,1209]" firstAuthor="WAGENER" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" pagination="17 - 85" refId="ref52229" refString="WAGENER B. 1881: Cassididae. Mittheilungen des Munchner Entomologischen Vereins 5: 17 - 85." type="journal article" year="1881">WAGENER (1881)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FCFFFB44FBA6FB09" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1881" box="[771,1048,1186,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FCFFFB44FBA6FB09" box="[771,1048,1186,1209]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Coptocycla nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having black dorsum with partly pale pronotum and elytra in basal two thirds with blood red (see 
<figureCitation id="77ED62B3FFF2FFD9FF6BFB04FF68FB49" box="[151,214,1250,1273]" captionStart="Figs 1–3" captionStartId="12.[151,187,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[216,1090,220,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-32@12.[161,1116,219,1542]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 1–3. Charidotis amazona sp. nov., holotype 1 – dorsal aspect; 2 – lateral aspect; 3 – head, antennae, and fore legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305727/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
Fig. 
<quantity id="282ED3D3FFF2FFD9FF35FB04FF68FB49" box="[201,214,1250,1273]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" unit="in" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FF00FB04FE19FB49" author="CHAMPION" box="[252,423,1250,1273]" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION 1894</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FE46FB04FDCCFB49" author="CHAMPION" box="[442,626,1250,1273]" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION (1894)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD14FB04FC75FB49" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[744,971,1250,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD14FB04FC75FB49" box="[744,971,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Coptocycla tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and separated it from the two previously mentioned taxa by different colouration (see 
<figureCitation id="77ED62B3FFF2FFD9FC67FAE4FC64FAA9" box="[923,986,1282,1305]" captionStart="Figs 1–3" captionStartId="12.[151,187,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[216,1090,220,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-32@12.[161,1116,219,1542]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 1–3. Charidotis amazona sp. nov., holotype 1 – dorsal aspect; 2 – lateral aspect; 3 – head, antennae, and fore legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305727/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
Fig. 
<quantity id="282ED3D3FFF2FFD9FC31FAE4FC64FAA9" box="[973,986,1282,1305]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" unit="in" value="3.0">3</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FC02FAE4FF6EFA89" author="CHAMPION" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION 1894</bibRefCitation>
). He also added that all three taxa have similar punctation of elytra formed by quite large and sparsely arranged punctures also extending on the explanate margin of elytra. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FC02FAA4FF61FAC9" author="CHAMPION" firstAuthor="CHAMPION" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">CHAMPION (1894)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FEA4FA84FE67FAC9" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[344,473,1378,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FEA4FA84FE67FAC9" box="[344,473,1378,1401]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">C. tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
stands nearest to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD6AFA84FB92FAC9" authority="Boheman, 1862" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[662,1068,1378,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD6AFA84FCC2FAC9" box="[662,892,1378,1401]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Coptocycla speculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FC7FFA84FB92FAC9" author="Boheman" box="[899,1068,1378,1401]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">Boheman, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Amazon Basin due to similar habitus and colouration. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FCFCFA64FC28FA29" author="SPAETH" box="[768,918,1410,1433]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
transferred all abovementioned taxa to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FE80FA44FE72FA09" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[380,460,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FE80FA44FE72FA09" box="[380,460,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD8FFA44FC92FA09" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1881" box="[627,812,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD8FFA44FC92FA09" box="[627,812,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FC90FA44FC58FA09" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[876,998,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FC90FA44FC58FA09" box="[876,998,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mentioned that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FF38FA24FEF8FA69" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[196,326,1474,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FF38FA24FEF8FA69" box="[196,326,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FE8BFA24FE42FA69" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[375,508,1474,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FE8BFA24FE42FA69" box="[375,508,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. speculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown to him, and described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FC8AFA24FF75FA49" authority="Spaeth, 1911" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FC8AFA24FBAFFA69" box="[886,1041,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. plagipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FBEBFA24FF75FA49" author="Spaeth" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">Spaeth, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFF2FFD9FEF1FA04FEC8FA49" box="[269,374,1506,1529]" name="Colombia" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and placed it in the same group as 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD11FA04FCDBFA49" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[749,869,1506,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD11FA04FCDBFA49" box="[749,869,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF2FFD8FF49F9E4FD4EFEC3" blockId="40.[151,1127,1026,1625]" lastBlockId="41.[113,1089,220,467]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="316" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
During my visits in various museums I had an opportunity to examine 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFF2FFD9FC4AF9E4FC50F9A9" box="[950,1006,1538,1561]" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">types</typeStatus>
of all abovemetioned taxa and I am reasonably certain that at least the three Central American taxa (
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FF5CF9A4FEA6F9E9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[160,280,1602,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FF5CF9A4FEA6F9E9" box="[160,280,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FEDAF9A4FE62F9E9" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1881" box="[294,476,1602,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FEDAF9A4FE62F9E9" box="[294,476,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">C. nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FDECF9A4FD2CF9E9" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[528,658,1602,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FDECF9A4FD2CF9E9" box="[528,658,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">C. tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are conspecific as I was unable to find any relevant morphological characters to separate them besides colouration and I thus synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FF8DFF1AFF4CFEA3" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1894" box="[113,242,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FF8DFF1AFF4CFEA3" box="[113,242,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">C. tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FED1FF1AFE1CFEA3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[301,418,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FED1FF1AFE1CFEA3" box="[301,418,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">C. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and confirm the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FD19FF1AFC27FEA3" authorityName="Wagener" authorityYear="1881" box="[741,921,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropunctata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FD19FF1AFC27FEA3" box="[741,921,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">C. nigropunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, I treat 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FF5BFEFAFE93FE83" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[167,301,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FF5BFEFAFE93FE83" box="[167,301,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">O. speculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species differing from 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FD73FEFAFCB8FE83" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[655,774,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FD73FEFAFCB8FE83" box="[655,774,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the stouter body and large size but as I mentioned under 
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FE4FFEDAFDFFFEE3" box="[435,577,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF3FFD8FE4FFEDAFD83FEE3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[435,573,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">O. speculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
future studies may demonstrate that all of them belong to a single, broadly distributed polymorphic species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFF3FFD8FF8DFE9AFE1AFE63" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF3FFD8FF8DFE9AFE1AFE63" blockId="41.[113,1089,220,467]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF3FFD8FF8DFE9AFEBAFE23" bold="true" box="[113,260,380,403]" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFF3FFD8FEF7FE9AFE3EFE23" box="[267,384,380,403]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF3FFD8FE73FE9AFD8DFE23" author="BOHEMAN" box="[399,563,380,403]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN 1862</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF3FFD8FDC2FE9AFD4AFE23" author="BOROWIEC" box="[574,756,380,403]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" pagination="615 - 722" refId="ref48513" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2009 c: New records of Neotropical tortoise beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 20: 615 - 722." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="c">BOROWIEC 2009c</bibRefCitation>
), French 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFF3FFD8FCA4FE9AFC15FE23" box="[856,939,380,403]" name="Guyana" pageId="41" pageNumber="316">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF3FFD8FC47FE9AFE9FFE03" author="BOROWIEC &amp; MORAGUES" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="41" pageNumber="316" pagination="247 - 278" refId="ref48540" refString="BOROWIEC L. &amp; MORAGUES G. 2005: Tortoise beetles of the French Guyana - a faunistic review (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 16: 247 - 278." type="journal article" year="2005">BOROWIEC &amp; MORAGUES 2005</bibRefCitation>
), 
